data.chText: （海、湖伸向陆地或岛屿间的）小湾，水湾
data.enText: a narrow strip of water that stretches into the land from the sea or a lake, or between islands

data.chText: （液体、空气或气体进入机器的）入口，进口
data.enText: an opening through which liquid, air or gas can enter a machine

means: (海、湖伸向陆地或岛屿间的)小湾，水湾
(液体、空气或气体进入机器的)入口，进口

tr: an opening through which fluid is admitted to a tube or container
an arm off of a larger body of water (often between rocky headlands)

value.def: An inlet is a narrow strip of water which goes from a sea or lake into the land.
value.tran: (海或湖伸向陆地的狭长)水湾，小湾，小港

value.def: An inlet is a part of a machine through which a flow of liquid enters.
